# ActivateMode — mission_control_node → mode_manager_node.
#
# Two-phase bring-up (mirrors alt_pipeline prepare / activate split):
#
#   activate=false  →  ~/setup + configure each node (SetMission /
#                      prepare). Nodes stay inactive; Numba JIT runs here.
#
#   activate=true   →  activate nodes prepared by the last prepare call
#                      (RuntimeControl open). Mission must match prepared.
#
# Empty mission deactivates+cleans up every autonomy node regardless of
# activate (tear down / mission_id=0).
#
# Mission values:
#   "trackdrive" | "autocross" | "accel" | "skidpad"
#
# reset_nodes holds autonomy node names to CLEAN-CYCLE on an activate
# (deactivate -> activate) so they re-run on_activate with fresh per-run
# state, while every other node is left untouched (already-active nodes are
# idempotently skipped). Empty for the normal path. Used by the free-run
# floor's go hand-off: control_node runs through the OFF/manual floor to log
# its would-be commands, then reset_nodes=[control_node] gives it a clean
# reset exactly at the Ready->Driving edge so the real run doesn't inherit
# the manual-lap state. Ignored for teardown (empty mission tears down all).
#
# Response field is `ok` (not `success`).

# ---------------- Request ----------------
string mission
bool activate
string[] reset_nodes

---
# ---------------- Response ----------------
bool ok
string message
